2 SENATE BILL 44
1 (b) A person is guilty of negligent driving if he drives a motor vehicle in a careless
2 or imprudent manner that endangers any property or the life or person of any individual.
3 (c) (1) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, A
4 PERSON CHARGED WITH A VIOLATION OF THIS SECTION THAT CONTRIBUTES TO AN
5 ACCIDENT THAT RESULTS IN THE DEATH OF ANOTHER:
6 (I) MUST APPEAR IN COURT; AND
7 (II) MAY NOT PREPAY THE FINE.
8 (2) AFTER A COURT HAS ISSUED A WRIT SETTING THE DATE, TIME,
9 AND PLACE FOR THE PERSON TO APPEAR, THE COURT MAY, FOR GOOD CAUSE
10 SHOWN:
11 (I) WAIVE THE REQUIREMENT TO APPEAR IN COURT; AND
12 (II) ALLOW THE PERSON TO ENTER A PLEA OF GUILTY AND
13 PREPAY THE FINE.
14 (D) A person convicted of a violation of subsection (a) of this section is subject to a
15 fine not exceeding $1,000.
16 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
17 October 1, 2025.

